	                                <p>Yep, the JsonResponse class should do all of this for you, but if you ever use the Response object directly with json_encode, definitely don't forget to set the Content-Type header exactly as <a data-dsq-mention="disqus_2puhm4cl8d:disqus" href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdisqus.com%2Fby%2Fdisqus_2PuHM4Cl8d%2F%3A2bwtuMqOxB7-LVVAx6mMs4ksOq8&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">Abou</a> said: this is what tells JavaScript how to parse the response.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
