	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2689767965" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2689767965" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Alice!</p><p>This is actually expected. The JavaScript makes an AJAX request every 2 seconds to check for new comments ( <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fknpuniversity%2Fsymfony%2Fblob%2Fmaster%2Ftutorial%2Fweb%2Fjs%2Fnotes.react.js%23L10%3AXbhmmAHjrJ2sL1q1WzesseGcYJA&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://github.com/knpuniversi...</a> ). This is called "polling" - it's a "cheap" way to get the "instant update" whenever someone makes a comment. In reality, if I want this type of functionality, I will usually use something like Pusher ( <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2FlaupiFrpar%2FLopiPusherBundle%3ASmstDIkHMcpt_GVzdxjemN1RxZM&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://github.com/laupiFrpar/...</a> ) to notify me instantly of when the changes happen. I would do this instead of making AJAX requests every XX seconds. But, you *are* seeing the expected behavior :).</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
