	                                <p>Hey Matt!</p><p>Hmm, it *is* possible that this is caused by an AJAX error from the /genus/octopus/notes endpoint. I would first debug the response that you're getting back after making the AJAX call - in the success function of notes.react.js around line 17 (success:function ()...). If the response did not contain the valid JSON (e.g. JSON with a notes key), then this would ultimately cause this.props.notes to be undefined. But, it could be something else too :). If you download the course code for this tutorial and use the "finish" directory - you could double-check and see if that works, then compare it to your code.</p><p>Let me know how it goes!</p>
